		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The aim of this project is to develop a new opto-thermal instrument matched to the specific requirements of in-vivo skin measurements.  It centres on a hand-held probe which connected to the excitation laser and infrared detector through optical fibres.  This new approach will overcome the shortcomes of the current bench-top instrument and allow opto-thermal measurement to be performed on any human skin side in-vivo.  Also, with a stepping motor scanner, it will enable in-vivo line-scan imaging to be performed for the first time which is essential for heterogeneous samples such as human skin.  These new features and capabilities will extend the application range of opto-thermal measurements in both biomedical (skin characterisation, optical biopsy etc) and in industrial (on-line monitoring, photothermal NDT etc) areas.  This proposed project will also make opto-thermal measurements quick and reliable, for wider acceptable and eventual routine use.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
